---
layout: layouts/base.njk
title: Contact Us - Get in Touch
description: Contact NEXT3LABS for software development and Linux server rescue in Singapore. Email, WhatsApp, or visit our office at Peck Seah Street. Emergency support available.
permalink: /contact/
---

<section class="page-header">
  <div class="container">
    <h1>Let's Talk</h1>
    <p class="lead">Got a project? Server emergency? Just want to chat about tech?</p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="contact-content">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="contact-grid">
      <div class="contact-info">
        <h2>Get in Touch</h2>
        <p>Fastest way to reach us is by email. We typically respond within a few hours during business days.</p>
        <p>For server emergencies, mention "URGENT" in your subject line.</p>

        <div class="contact-details">
          <div class="contact-item">
            <h3>Email</h3>
            <p><a href="mailto:{{ site.company.email }}">{{ site.company.email }}</a></p>
          </div>

          <div class="contact-item">
            <h3>WhatsApp</h3>
            <p><a href="https://wa.me/6587721895" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">+65 8772 1895</a></p>
            <p style="font-size: 0.9rem; color: #666; margin-top: 0.5rem;">Quick questions? Chat with us on WhatsApp</p>
          </div>

          <div class="contact-item">
            <h3>Location</h3>
            <p><strong>{{ site.company.legalName }}</strong><br>
            {{ site.company.address.street }}<br>
            {{ site.company.address.building }}<br>
            {{ site.company.city }} {{ site.company.address.postal }}</p>
            <p style="margin-top: 0.5rem;">UEN: {{ site.company.uen }}</p>
          </div>

          <div class="contact-item">
            <h3>Working Hours</h3>
            <p>Monday - Friday: 9:00 AM - 6:00 PM SGT<br>
            Emergency support available 24/7 for existing clients</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="contact-form">
        <h3>Send Us a Message</h3>
        <p style="margin-bottom: 1.5rem;">Or just email us directly at <a href="mailto:{{ site.company.email }}">{{ site.company.email }}</a></p>

        <form id="contact-form" method="POST" onsubmit="return sendContactEmail(event)">
          <div class="form-group">
            <label for="name">Name</label>
            <input type="text" id="name" name="name" required>
          </div>

          <div class="form-group">
            <label for="email">Email</label>
            <input type="email" id="email" name="email" required>
          </div>

          <div class="form-group">
            <label for="message">Message</label>
            <textarea id="message" name="message" rows="5" required placeholder="Tell us about your project or what you need help with..."></textarea>
          </div>

          <button type="submit" class="btn btn-primary">Send Message</button>
        </form>

        <!--
          The form opens the visitor's email client pre-filled to {{ site.company.email }}.
          This guarantees a working contact path with no backend. Swap onsubmit for a
          POST endpoint (Formspree / serverless / etc.) when one is provisioned.
        -->
        <script>
          function sendContactEmail(event) {
            event.preventDefault();
            var name = document.getElementById('name').value.trim();
            var email = document.getElementById('email').value.trim();
            var message = document.getElementById('message').value.trim();
            var subject = 'Website enquiry from ' + (name || 'a visitor');
            var body =
              'Name: ' + name + '\n' +
              'Email: ' + email + '\n\n' +
              message;
            window.location.href = 'mailto:{{ site.company.email }}'
              + '?subject=' + encodeURIComponent(subject)
              + '&body=' + encodeURIComponent(body);
            return false;
          }
        </script>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
